To make the text in the popup window match the text on the wheel, you need to adjust the text alignment and rotation in the `drawWheel` method. Specifically, you need to rotate the text to match the angle of the sector it's in.

Here's the modified code:
```javascript
drawWheel(currentAngle = 0) {
  //...

  for (let i = 0; i < numSectors; i++) {
    const startAngle = i * sectorAngle;
    const endAngle = (i + 1) * sectorAngle;

    //...

    const textAngle = startAngle + sectorAngle / 2;
    const textX = this.centerX + Math.cos(textAngle) * this.radius * 0.8;
    const textY = this.centerY + Math.sin(textAngle) * this.radius * 0.8;

    this.ctx.save();
    this.ctx.translate(textX, textY);
    this.ctx.rotate(textAngle + Math.PI / 2); // Add this line to rotate the text
    this.ctx.textAlign = 'center';
    this.ctx.textBaseline ='middle';
    this.ctx.font = '20px fantasy';
    this.ctx.fillStyle = '#fff';
    this.ctx.fillText(text, 0, 0);
    this.ctx.restore();

    //...
  }
}
```
In this code, I added the line `this.ctx.rotate(textAngle + Math.PI / 2)` to rotate the text to match the angle of the sector it's in. This will make the text on the wheel match the text in the popup window.

Note that you may need to adjust the rotation angle depending on the specific design of your wheel and popup window.

