    }
    //...
}
```

In this example, the `isValidEmail` function checks if the email address contains an '@' symbol and a '.' symbol, and if the '@' symbol comes before the '.' symbol. This is a very basic email validation and you may want to improve it based on your requirements.

Also, you can add a boolean variable to your Student class to track if the email is valid or not. You can set this variable in the `setEmailAddress` function and then use it in the `print` function to display "Invalid Email" if the email is not valid.

